Program: The Documentary
Title: Skiing Mount Lebanon
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csx8wr
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 2 Apr 2018
Karl Sharro experiences the Middle East from the unique perspective of a Lebanese ski resort, an eye in the hurricane of the surrounding conflicts. Here, different nationalities and religions escape the politics and differences to enjoy a shared passion – winter sports – in mountainous regions that are laden with sacred symbolism for the Lebanese. (Photo: Lebanese and tourists ski at the Lebanese resort of Faraya, north-east of Beirut. Credit: Joseph Eid/AFP/Getty Images) Show less